    <ns3948:title xmlns:ns3948="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Buttons</ns3948:title>
    <ns3949:para xmlns:ns3949="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Buttons have a true (pressed) and a false (released) state. They are often used to request
        a specific action. The root for Java buttons is <ns3950:literal xmlns:ns3950="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">AbstractButton</ns3950:literal> with
        <ns3951:literal xmlns:ns3951="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JButton</ns3951:literal> the standard press-button class. Other button specializations
        include toggle buttons like check boxes and radio buttons as well as menu items. The class
        hierarchy is shown below.</ns3949:para>
    <ns3952:para xmlns:ns3952="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">All buttons can be enabled or disabled </ns3952:para>
